Mineral saturation states were evaluated to assess the groundwater system’s equilibrium conditions and precipitation/dissolution potential for major carbonate minerals50,51. The saturation index (SI) for each mineral phase was calculated using the fundamental relationship:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:SI=\text{l}\text{o}\text{g}(\text{I}\text{A}\text{P}/\text{K}\text{t})$$\end{document}

Primary Chloro-Alkaline Index:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\text{C}\text{A}\text{I}_{1}\:=\:[\text{C}\text{l} ^{-}\:-\:(\text{N}\text{a}^{+}\:+\:\text{K}^{+}\left)\right]/\text{C}\text{l}^{-}$$\end{document}

Secondary Chloro-Alkaline Index:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\text{C}\text{A}\text{I}_{2}\:=\:[\text{C}\text{l}^{-}\:-\:(\text{N}\text{a}^{+}\:+\:\text{K}^{+}\left)\right]/(\text{S}\text{O}_{4}{^{2-}}+\:+\:\text{H}\text{C}\text{O}_{3}^{-})$$\end{document}

The parameters weights were calculated based on WHO (2017) guidelines using the following steps:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:Wi\:=\frac{K}{Sn}$$\end{document}

Where, Wi is the relative weight, Sn is the WHO standard value for each parameter, and K is a proportionality constant calculated as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:K\:=\frac{1}{\sum\:\left(\frac{1}{Sn}\right)}$$\end{document}

The Water Quality Index is calculated using formula27,56,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\text{W}\text{Q}\text{I}=\frac{{\Sigma\:}\text{W}\text{i}\text{Q}\text{i}}{{\Sigma\:}\text{W}\text{i}}$$\end{document}

Where, WQI - Water Quality Index (values between 0 and 100), Wi - weight of the ith parameter and Qi - the quality rating or sub-index of the ith parameter.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:Qi\:=\left(\frac{Vn}{Sn}\right)*100$$\end{document}
